          <p class='first-para'>
            Much of the revenue and customs work is now outsourced, where confidential information is handled by big international IT companies&#x2014;previously EDS in the Revenue and now Capgemini. What terms and conditions in regard to that are applied to the employees of those companies? Is a declaration required of them? I should imagine that the
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_259gc' title='Col. 259GC &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c259GC' name='column_259gc' href='#column_259gc' rel='bookmark'>259GC</a>
            same terms would apply across the board, whether the people have direct appointments within Customs or the Inland Revenue or are in the outsourced companies.
          </p>
